### 10. Missing Concepts (Critical Additions)

#### 10.1 Request ID Tracing
Every response must include a `request_id` for end-to-end observability. Generate at the gateway or view layer, propagate through all layers.

#### 10.2 Retry Hints
For transient errors, include machine-readable retry guidance:
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "RATE_LIMIT__EXCEEDED",
    "details": {
      "retry_after_seconds": 30,
      "reset_at": "2024-10-01T12:00:00Z"
    }
  }
}
```

#### 10.3 Error Severity Classification
Errors should be internally classified for monitoring (not exposed to clients):
- `CLIENT_ERROR` — 4xx, user fixable
- `SERVER_ERROR` — 5xx, requires engineering attention
- `TRANSIENT_ERROR` — retry-eligible

#### 10.4 Pagination Errors
```json
{ "code": "VALIDATION__INVALID_CURSOR" }
{ "code": "VALIDATION__PAGE_OUT_OF_RANGE" }
```

