## QUICK REFERENCE — Decision Tree

```
New error code needed?
│
├─ Does an existing code cover this case? ──► YES → Use it. Done.
│
└─ NO → Pick namespace:
         ├─ Auth/token/session issue? ──────────► AUTH__
         ├─ User entity operation? ─────────────► USER__
         ├─ Input/form validation? ─────────────► VALIDATION__
         ├─ Access control / roles? ────────────► PERMISSION__
         ├─ Billing / subscription? ────────────► PAYMENT__
         ├─ File / storage? ────────────────────► MEDIA__
         ├─ External API / webhook? ────────────► INTEGRATION__
         ├─ Too many requests? ─────────────────► RATE_LIMIT__
         └─ Everything else / unhandled? ───────► INTERNAL__

Name the condition: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE, verb-last, no _ERROR suffix
Combine: NAMESPACE__CONDITION
Add to errors/catalog.py with http_status + description + since_version
```
